{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cataracts/diagnosis/diagnosis-adult/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"528c7027-507f-53fe-9c7d-d7d6bd0ad969","slug":"diagnosis-adult","fullItemName":"Diagnosis - adult","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6aebea6e-7852-420e-9675-6778c8eac46e --><h2>How should I diagnose a cataract in an adult?</h2><!-- end field 6aebea6e-7852-420e-9675-6778c8eac46e -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 4c81e583-cdee-4448-a50f-84dd636f08ea --><!-- begin field 7c8a34f9-7155-4360-a512-e859213e6d6f --><ul><li><strong>Take a history and ask about:</strong><ul><li>The clinical features. </li><li>Symptom onset, duration, and fluctuation over time. </li><li>The impact of symptoms on daily life.</li><li>Occular history.</li><li>Risk factors for cataract. </li><li>Current medicines and medical conditions.</li><li>Previous surgery. </li></ul></li><li><strong>Assess:</strong> <ul><li>Visual acuity<strong> </strong>— for example, with a Snellen chart.</li><li>Occular alignment and motility. </li><li>Pupillary function. </li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine the: </strong><ul><li>Eyes using an ophthalmoscope —<strong> </strong>opacity of the lens may be observed through defects in the red reflex if cataract is present.</li><li>Eyelid position and character, lashes, lacrimal apparatus and tear function, orbit, and pertinent facial features. </li></ul></li><li><strong>Investigations </strong>— the equipment and expertise are not commonly available in primary care and referral to an optometrist or ophthalmologist is usually required. Investigations may include:<ul><li>Slit-lamp examination to physically examine the lens — an opacity can be seen in the lens if cataract is present.</li><li>Intraocular pressure measurement.</li><li>A glare vision test. </li></ul></li><li><strong>There is no single test or measure that adequately describes the effect of a cataract on a patient’s visual status or functional ability. </strong></li></ul><!-- end field 7c8a34f9-7155-4360-a512-e859213e6d6f --><!-- end item 4c81e583-cdee-4448-a50f-84dd636f08ea -->","topic":{"id":"eeb34712-def5-5b38-9125-fec8925c1bcc","topicId":"9a3fe0f5-1b06-4ff6-9a79-2ed4a8f4b2c5","topicName":"Cataracts","slug":"cataracts","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"90f4d5e6-8dee-54a2-b535-a3280c9ff7e9","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"da1f4019-d02d-523b-80ce-e4ba8579b43d","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"87a3b79a-dbff-50b1-a10c-fc54f60080f3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"cd79c0cf-e5a8-5fb6-99af-3d9e0eaf4b28","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"d0c360ad-3631-54ab-809e-570769cd5aa1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"8af6938b-ae1b-5c2a-8b8c-826edbed8669","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed0ddb2-07a6-5c9e-86b8-740894cd88e7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d3db836f-68b9-5c32-bb04-1d6c9b755015","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"78ff1c73-3038-544d-829b-9c4fa6e07ea0","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"656fb8f7-2abd-5f0f-ad42-29abf4c1f6f6","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"b62da534-cf57-5fe0-b8ab-b615d0f453db","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"aeadf6c4-c840-5132-8088-24333b53ef51","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"72d37d02-73ec-5804-8b0b-ec8c9f598bd8","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"7c9d7f21-34f0-5df8-a1d4-8826a0ace32c","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"0a895e5e-b9bb-54b2-9872-590