me":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"39990bfd-9566-5252-b7b1-ecb7a6fc4541","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"e87190fb-3f26-5832-b880-cec44fe6b479","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"40e3972b-8e1c-514b-a557-e69d23d2f3e9","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-adf","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d08ab66a-3e15-4a8c-b15e-f8f99b698c31 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field d08ab66a-3e15-4a8c-b15e-f8f99b698c31 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item adfe1ee4-fede-4876-b96a-689b334a5ce8 --><!-- begin field 51c0a240-46f7-480f-b732-32ea9dc7ebd4 --><p>These recommendations are based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline <em>Cataracts in adults: management</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>], the American Association of Ophthalmology (AAO) guidelines <em>Cataract in the adult eye preferred practice pattern </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">AAO, 2016a</a>] and <em>Comprehensive adult medical eye evaluation preferred practice pattern guidelines </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">AAO, 2016b</a>], the British Medical Journal (BMJ) best practice guide <em>Cataracts</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>], and expert opinion in a narrative review <em>Care of older adults: role of primary care physicians in the treatment of cataracts and macular degeneration</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cataracts/references/\">Marra, 2016</a>]. </p><!-- end field 51c0a240-46f7-480f-b732-32ea9dc7ebd4 --><!-- end item adfe1ee4-fede-4876-b96a-689b334a5ce8 -->","subChapters":